<title type="html"><![CDATA[Switching from Gentoo to Ubuntu]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7246&amp;p=71107#p71107"><![CDATA[
Hey all. I've been seriously considering switching my webserver/email-server/blog/router/CVS-server/bugzilla/etc/etc machine from gentoo to ubuntu.<br /><br />I started learning linux on gentoo a loooooooong time ago.  And talk about diving headfirst into linux - dang!  But I did learn a ton...but now I'm just tired of having to compile everything when I want to upgrade the system and also having to deal with all the dependency issues of portage (i.e. gentoo's package manager).  I think it would be nice to have a much more user-friendly upgrade and package install process from this point forward.  Gentoo is just too much of a maintenance hassle and manual/tedious labor process as far as I'm concerned.<br /><br />Anyone have any thoughts on this?  Just curious.<br /><br />pz!<br /><br />Jonathon<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3962">jwdonal</a> — Sun Dec 05, 2010 8:30 pm</p><hr />
